//userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/126/278288.jpg"}]}, {"name": "Jeffrey Lewis", "url": "http://www.last.fm/music/Jeffrey+Lewis", "image": [{"size": "small", "#text": "http://userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/34/329370.jpg"}, {"size": "medium", "#text": "http://userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/64/329370.jpg\u003E"}, {"size": "large", "#text": "http://userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/126/329370.jpg"}]}, {"name": "Adam Green", "url": "http://www.last.fm/music/Adam+Green", "image": [{"size": "small", "#text": "http://userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/34/388722.jpg"}, {"size": "medium", "#text": "http://userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/64/388722.jpg\u003E"}, {"size": "large", "#text": "http://userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/126/388722.jpg"}]}, {"name": "Mateo Messina", "url": "http://www.last.fm/music/Mateo+Messina", "image": [{"size": "small", "#text": "http://userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/34/3815488.jpg"}, {"size": "medium", "#text": "http://userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/64/3815488.jpg\u003E"}, {"size": "large", "#text": "http://userserve-ak.last.fm/serve/126/3815488.jpg"}]}]}, "url": "http://www.last.fm/music/Kimya+Dawson", "mbid": "ba99a190-6065-4930-be3d-55ecc48e365d", "streamable": "1", "bio": {"published": "Mon, 20 Oct 2008 23:38:47 +0000", "content": "\u003Cstrong\u003EKimya Dawson\u003C/strong\u003E (born 17th November 1972) is an Olympia-based singer-songwriter, and a prominent part of the \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/tag/anti-folk\" class=\"bbcode_tag\" rel=\"tag\"\u003Eanti-folk\u003C/a\u003E movement.\n\n Dawson became well known as a member of \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/The+Moldy+Peaches\" class=\"bbcode_artist\"\u003EThe Moldy Peaches\u003C/a\u003E. Since the Moldy Peaches took a break from performing and recording in 2004, Dawson has released a string of lo-fi homemade albums, and toured widely in North America and Europe.\n\n In 2005 the \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/Pharmacy\" class=\"bbcode_artist\"\u003EPharmacy\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/+noredirect/Matty+Popchart\" class=\"bbcode_artist\"\u003EMatty Popchart\u003C/a\u003E performed as her backing band on a U.S. tour.  In 2006 she collaborated with a number of friends to make a group, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/Antsy+Pants\" class=\"bbcode_artist\"\u003EAntsy Pants\u003C/a\u003E, that recorded and released an album on Plan It X Records.\n\n Dawson's songs are featured in the films \u003Cem\u003EThe Guatemalan Handshake\u003C/em\u003E and \u003Cem\u003EGlue\u003C/em\u003E, both of which were shown at the Olympia Film Festival in November 2007. There is also some of her music in the cult movie \u003Cem\u003EJuno\u003C/em\u003E, which is the fastest selling film soundtrack since Saturday Night Fever.\n\n She is currently working on \u003Cem\u003EAlphabutt\u003C/em\u003E, an album of songs for babies.", "summary": "Kimya Dawson (born 17th November 1972) is an Olympia-based singer-songwriter, and a prominent part of the \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/tag/anti-folk\" class=\"bbcode_tag\" rel=\"tag\"\u003Eanti-folk\u003C/a\u003E movement.  Dawson became well known as a member of \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/The+Moldy+Peaches\" class=\"bbcode_artist\"\u003EThe Moldy Peaches\u003C/a\u003E. Since the Moldy Peaches took a break from performing and recording in 2004, Dawson has released a string of lo-fi homemade albums, and toured widely in North America and Europe.  In 2005 the \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/Pharmacy\" class=\"bbcode_artist\"\u003EPharmacy\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/+noredirect/Matty+Popchart\" class=\"bbcode_artist\"\u003EMatty Popchart\u003C/a\u003E performed as her backing band on a U.S. tour.  In 2006 she collaborated with a number of friends to make a group, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.last.fm/music/Antsy+Pants\" class=\"bbcode_artist\"\u003EAntsy Pants\u003C/a\u003E, that recorded and released an album on Plan It X Records. "}, "image": [{"size": "small", "#text": "http://u